  "content": {
    "visible_text": "Red Belt Second and First Gup Fire is the focus element at Red Belt, as students begin to learn and define speed, potential energy, the electricity in motion, and redirection. At the level of Red Belt, students truly step in to the role of teacher and begin to understand what it is to teach martial arts. Red Belt Curriculum Form One-Steps Techniques High Red Belt Curriculum Form Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
